DateTimeX-ymdhms version 0.0.2

Adds the methods ymdhms and ymdhm to DateTime objects so that you can
now easily do $dt->ymdhms to produce "date time"
presentations. (Basically ISO-8601 without the T).

Its a bit long - 6 chars - but its easy to remember because its the
combination of "ymd" and "hms"

Also adds ymdhm, same as above only without seconds.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install


DEPENDENCIES

None.


